<TITLE> Exams in Khulna, Barisal schools deferred </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 19 (bdnews24.com)  The government has directed the primary, secondary schools and madrasas of Khulna and Barisal divisions to defer annual examinations for one month, a senior government official said Monday. The examinations will now begin on December 26 instead of November 24. Education secretary Momtazul Islam Monday told reporters, "Examinations have been deferred until December 26." Exams can be arranged before the date if any institution wants," he said. The government also rescheduled scholarship examinations. The junior scholarship examinations will now be held on January 8-9 instead of December 10-11. Primary scholarship examinations will be held on December 17-18. An official of the ministry said schools were earlier asked to publish results of qualification tests for Secondary School Certificate examinations by January 6. The ministry asked the institutions to reschedule the tests too. But the education secretary said that an inter-board committee would take a decision on the matter three days later. An estimate of the Directorate of Secondary and Higher Education showed that Cyclone Sidr damaged 338 educational institutions entirely in the coastal districts. Nearly 643 institutions were damaged partly. Momtazul Islam said that a Tk 42.43 crore proposal was made for repairing 3,541 educational institutions damaged by the storm. bdnews
